# Summary for Coffee Shop Sales Dashboard
📊 Project Name: Coffee Shop Sales Analysis
🔍 Description: This project analyzes sales data from a coffee shop to identify key trends, including customer preferences, peak hours, and revenue distribution. A Power BI dashboard has been created to visualize insights.

# Key Insights from the Dashboard:
☕ Total Sales: $698,812.33
👣 Total Footfall: 149,116 customers
💰 Average Bill per Person: $4.68
🛒 Average Order Size: 1.44 items

# Dashboard Highlights:
⏳ Peak Hours: Sales peak between 8 AM and 11 AM, then gradually decline.
🏢 Top Store Locations: Hell’s Kitchen and Lower Manhattan generate the highest revenue.
🥇 Best-Selling Product Categories: Coffee and Tea lead the sales, followed by bakery items.
🎯 Customer Preferences:
Size Distribution: 30% prefer large-sized drinks, 31% opt for regular.
Popular Product Types: Barista Espresso, Brewed Black Tea, and Gourmet Brewed Coffee.
Sales Trend by Day: Friday sees the highest sales, while Saturday has the lowest.

# Technologies Used:
Excel, Pivot table.
